events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Brooklyn Nets

headlines.description: — The Brooklyn Nets just needed any home win, so they weren't about to complain when one that appeared to be coming easily almost didn't come at all.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nets edge Spurs on Thomas' OT basket to end 5-game home skid

headlines.description: — Amir Coffey tied a career-high with 21 points and Serge Ibaka added 16 to lead the Los Angeles Clippers to a 106-93 win over the Atlanta Hawks on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Coffey lifts Clippers to 106-93 win over Hawks

headlines.description: — Kyle Kuzma had 27 points and a career-best 22 rebounds, Bradley Beal scored 20 points and the Washington Wizards rallied in the fourth quarter to beat the Orlando Magic 102-100 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kuzma's 22 boards lift Wizards over Magic 102-100

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Toronto Raptors

headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam had 29 points and 10 rebounds, Fred VanVleet scored 32 points and the Toronto Raptors extended their winning streak to a season-high six games with a 105-101 win over the New Orleans Pelicans on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Siakam scores 29, Raptors beat Pelicans for 6th straight win

headlines.description: — Karl-Anthony Towns scored a season-high 40 points, D’Angelo Russell added 22 points and 10 assists and the Minnesota Timberwolves won their fourth straight game, beating the Houston Rockets 141-123 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Towns' season-high 40 points leads Minnesota over Houston

events.name: Denver Nuggets at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 22 points and 18 rebounds to help the Denver Nuggets beat the Oklahoma City Thunder 99-95 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic has 22 points, 18 rebounds, Nuggets beat Thunder 99-95

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic had 22 points, 14 rebounds and 14 assists for his third triple-double of the season as the Dallas Mavericks beat Chicago 113-99 on Sunday night for their season-best sixth straight win while snapping the Bulls’ nine-game winning streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic has triple-double, Mavericks beat Bulls 113-99

events.name: Cleveland Cavaliers at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Klay Thompson couldn’t wait to get his first shot up after more than 2 1/2 years away.
headlines.shortLinkText: Klay Thompson has 17 points in return, Warriors beat Cavs

events.name: Sacramento Kings at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Anfernee Simons led all scorers with 31 points and the Portland Trail Blazers handed the Sacramento Kings their fourth straight loss, 103-88 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anfernee Simons scores 31, Portland beats Sacramento 103-88

events.name: Memphis Grizzlies at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — The Memphis Grizzlies set a franchise record with their ninth straight win, getting 16 points and a breathtaking block from Ja Morant in a 127-119 victory over the Los Angeles Lakers on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morant's dazzling block lifts Grizzlies to 9th straight win
